results.name: a(n) = A179926(A025487(n)).
comment: Terms in A179926 are only determined by their prime signature. A025487 gives the least positive integer having its prime signature. Combining these sequences removes a lot of duplicates making it somewhat easier to show terms.
link: David A. Corneth, Prime signatures for some k and the corresponding values for A179926(k).
